WEBVTT

00:00.601 --> 00:03.002
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

00:03.004 --> 00:04.470
Charlotte?

00:04.472 --> 00:06.138
Get me jake ballard.

00:06.140 --> 00:08.307
Find cyrus, and i want the heads
of the c.I.A., the fbi,

00:08.309 --> 00:12.044
And the nsa in my office
yesterday.

00:12.046 --> 00:15.047
Did you hear me?
Yes, sir. Only...

00:15.049 --> 00:15.781
Uh...

00:15.783 --> 00:19.318
Agent fielding.

00:19.320 --> 00:21.320
I didn't call for
the secret service.

00:21.322 --> 00:22.788
Can i help you?

00:22.790 --> 00:25.157
We're here to help<i> you,</i>
mr. President.

00:25.159 --> 00:28.027
[ door closes ]
help<i> me?</i>

00:28.029 --> 00:29.562
The vice president
thought

00:29.563 --> 00:31.096
You would have trouble
following his instructions --

00:31.098 --> 00:32.765
Staying on the straight
and narrow,

00:32.767 --> 00:34.433
Not calling in
your friends in the fbi,

00:34.435 --> 00:36.602
The c.I.A., the nsa.

00:36.604 --> 00:38.270
He told us it would
be difficult for you --

00:38.272 --> 00:40.039
Not looking
for miss pope.

00:40.041 --> 00:42.041
He told us you would need
our support.

00:42.043 --> 00:43.542
Well, that's why we're here,
mr. President --

00:43.544 --> 00:46.078
To support you, to help you,
to watch you.

00:46.080 --> 00:49.548
The secret service
takes their orders from me,

00:49.550 --> 00:51.650
Not the vice president.

00:51.652 --> 00:53.786
[ inhales deeply ]

00:53.788 --> 00:56.822
I don't think
that i've been clear.

00:56.824 --> 00:59.458
I'm not talking about
just the secret service.

00:59.460 --> 01:03.195
There's also white house aides,
pages, staff, military guards,

01:03.197 --> 01:05.197
A couple of secretaries,

01:05.199 --> 01:08.834
Oh, and a few of the valets
and butlers in the residence.

01:08.836 --> 01:13.205
Consider us all
your support group.

01:13.207 --> 01:15.707
We're watching you,
keeping an eye on you --

01:15.709 --> 01:17.543
All of us at all times.

01:17.545 --> 01:20.679
Cameras, listening devices,
every phone call,

01:20.681 --> 01:22.848
Every toilet flush.

01:22.850 --> 01:25.517
See? We care.

01:25.519 --> 01:28.821
You should be grateful
for all this support.

01:28.823 --> 01:31.723
It would be a shame if miss pope
was beheaded.

01:31.725 --> 01:34.560
Don't you agree,
mr. President?

01:34.562 --> 01:36.762
They don't call this
the crown jewel

01:36.764 --> 01:39.798
Of the american prison system
for nothing.

01:39.800 --> 01:42.701
We'll be seeing you...
Sir.

01:42.703 --> 01:45.437
[ door opens ]

01:49.276 --> 01:51.343
[ door closes ]

01:53.614 --> 01:56.181
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

01:59.520 --> 02:01.253
Glad you're here.

02:01.255 --> 02:03.122
Thought you'd be gone
for the night.

02:03.124 --> 02:04.457
With all i have
to get home to?

02:04.458 --> 02:05.791
Who<i> do</i> you put
on your guest list

02:05.793 --> 02:08.894
For your arranged marriage
to an opportunistic sex worker?

02:08.896 --> 02:10.729
I need you to gather
the joint chiefs

02:10.731 --> 02:11.830
First thing
in the morning.

02:11.832 --> 02:14.600
You all right, sir?

02:14.602 --> 02:15.767
I'm fine.

02:15.769 --> 02:18.137
Are we talking
about west angola?

02:18.139 --> 02:20.172
I thought direct military action
had been taken off the table.

02:20.174 --> 02:22.307
Well, now it's back on.
Joint chiefs -- first thing, cy.

02:24.678 --> 02:27.346
Mellie: I spoke
to a couple of schools today

02:27.348 --> 02:28.647
About volunteerism,

02:28.649 --> 02:30.649
Giving back to the community,
and no one listened.

02:30.651 --> 02:33.318
No one cared,
including me.

02:33.320 --> 02:36.155
Oh, and they changed
my agents today.

02:36.157 --> 02:37.823
No warning.

02:37.825 --> 02:39.825
I have to talk
to the secret service.

02:39.827 --> 02:42.494
You get used to people.
Then they're gone.

02:42.496 --> 02:43.795
It's...

02:43.797 --> 02:46.165
[ sighs ]

02:46.167 --> 02:48.200
Dress.

02:52.706 --> 02:53.705
[ zipper closes ]

02:53.707 --> 02:55.874
[ sighs ]

02:55.876 --> 02:57.309
Necklace.

03:02.816 --> 03:05.784
You're awfully quiet.
Everything all right?

03:05.786 --> 03:08.320
Yeah, it's fine.
Just...

03:08.322 --> 03:09.755
Long day.

03:09.757 --> 03:11.356
Hmm.

03:13.861 --> 03:16.228
It's caught
in your hair.

03:16.230 --> 03:18.730
[ sighs ]

03:18.732 --> 03:20.866
I started sleeping
with andrew again.

03:20.868 --> 03:23.735
Not that long ago.

03:23.737 --> 03:25.737
I mean,
obviously before i found out

03:25.739 --> 03:29.608
He was also sleeping
with elizabeth north.

03:29.610 --> 03:32.945
I wasn't gonna tell you
for so many reasons.

03:32.947 --> 03:36.782
It's humiliating,
but...

03:36.784 --> 03:39.918
We're partners now,
right?

03:39.920 --> 03:41.787
I don't want us
to have to hide anything

03:41.789 --> 03:43.855
From each other
anymore.

03:47.962 --> 03:51.463
I thought...
Being with him

03:51.465 --> 03:55.467
Would make me happy the way
olivia makes you happy.

03:55.469 --> 03:59.304
I thought he would actually
be there for me.

03:59.306 --> 04:02.874
I thought he was my chance.
But...

04:02.876 --> 04:06.545
Now i think this is better --
what we have.

04:06.547 --> 04:08.714
It's a partnership.
It's clear.

04:08.716 --> 04:09.982
[ inhales sharply ]

04:09.984 --> 04:13.352
The things we've done.
[ sighs ]

04:13.354 --> 04:15.988
You know my dirty secrets.
I know yours.

04:15.990 --> 04:19.358
The election --

04:19.360 --> 04:22.928
Stop...Talking.

04:30.804 --> 04:32.771
[ scoffs ]

04:32.773 --> 04:33.939
Fine!

04:33.941 --> 04:35.974
[ door slams ]

04:38.646 --> 04:40.345
Andrew: Mister president,
i hope you're calling

04:40.347 --> 04:42.481
To tell me you've started
dropping bombs.

04:42.483 --> 04:43.815
I need something
from you.

04:43.817 --> 04:45.884
You're in no position
to make requests.

04:45.886 --> 04:47.369
I'm in a position
to make this one.

04:47.370 --> 04:48.853
I'm not going to do
a single thing you've asked

04:48.856 --> 04:51.407
Until
i have proof of life.

04:51.408 --> 04:53.959
You trying to buy yourself
some time, mister president?

04:53.961 --> 04:56.962
I'm the only person
on earth

04:56.964 --> 04:59.431
Who can give you your war,
andrew.

04:59.433 --> 05:02.734
Olivia pope could be halfway
around the world by now

05:02.736 --> 05:04.936
As far as either one
of us knows.

05:04.938 --> 05:08.607
I've been assured
she'll be kept alive,

05:08.609 --> 05:10.609
But i'm afraid
that's all i can offer.

05:10.611 --> 05:13.612
Then i'm afraid i can't offer
you anything at all.

05:13.614 --> 05:15.580
Proof of life.

05:15.582 --> 05:18.650
You want your war?
I want to know she's safe.

05:18.652 --> 05:19.951
Those are my terms,

05:19.953 --> 05:23.355
And nothing gets done
until you meet them.

05:29.830 --> 05:32.864
[ voice breaking ]
my name is olivia pope,

05:32.866 --> 05:37.569
And this is a copy of today's
<i>clarion international.</i>

05:37.571 --> 05:40.872
I have been taken
against my will.

05:40.874 --> 05:43.508
I have been offered
food and water,

05:43.510 --> 05:47.346
And i have not been tortured
or abused in any way,

05:47.348 --> 05:49.815
Which you know damn well
is a lie.
Stop.

05:49.817 --> 05:52.684
Did you see
the guards outside?

05:52.686 --> 05:55.787
Now...

05:55.789 --> 05:58.390
If i wasn't here
to protect you

05:58.392 --> 06:01.593
And keep things
civilized...

06:01.595 --> 06:03.762
They would tear you
to pieces.

06:05.933 --> 06:06.898
Now...

06:06.900 --> 06:09.968
Read the card.

06:16.009 --> 06:20.011
[ breathing raggedly ]

06:20.013 --> 06:22.013
[ crying ] i need...

06:22.015 --> 06:24.783
A glass of water, please.

06:40.401 --> 06:41.933
[ sniffs ]

06:48.909 --> 06:51.943
My name is olivia pope,

06:51.945 --> 06:54.980
And this is a copy of today's
<i>clarion international.</i>

06:54.982 --> 06:58.817
I have been taken
against my will.

06:58.819 --> 07:01.553
I have been offered food
and water,

07:01.555 --> 07:03.855
And i have not been tortured
or abused in any way.

07:03.857 --> 07:08.026
To ensure my continued safety,
you must de--

07:08.028 --> 07:12.798
Declare war on the nation
of west angola.

07:24.545 --> 07:27.712
<i>Do this within</i>
<i>the next 48 hours,</i>

07:27.714 --> 07:29.965
<i>And no harm will come to me.</i>

07:29.966 --> 07:32.217
[<i> voice breaking</i> ]
<i>refuse, and i will be killed.</i>

07:32.219 --> 07:34.052
Wait a minute.
I only saw it once.

07:34.054 --> 07:35.120
I need --
your copy.

07:35.122 --> 07:37.222
Watch it as many times
as you want.

07:37.224 --> 07:39.825
Have fun.

07:44.865 --> 07:47.599
[ sighs ] no reading under
the covers tonight, okay?

07:47.601 --> 07:49.000
"bed" means bed.

07:49.002 --> 07:52.204
Now, what do we say?

07:52.206 --> 07:53.538
Good night, room.

07:53.540 --> 07:55.874
Good night, moon.

07:55.876 --> 07:57.008
Good night, jane.

07:57.010 --> 08:00.245
Hmm.

08:04.918 --> 08:06.651
[ muffled scream ]

08:06.653 --> 08:08.487
[ breathing rapidly ]

08:08.489 --> 08:09.721
Where is olivia?

08:09.723 --> 08:11.022
I don't know!
I don't know!

08:11.024 --> 08:12.724
Please, let me go.

08:12.726 --> 08:14.726
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh, shh,
shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

08:14.728 --> 08:16.862
Someone took olivia.

08:16.863 --> 08:18.997
Tell me what you know,
or i will go in that room,

08:18.999 --> 08:22.801
And i will cut that girl open
in her bed and make you watch.

08:22.803 --> 08:23.935
[ crying ]
i don't know who took her.

08:23.937 --> 08:25.937
I swear.

08:25.939 --> 08:28.273
But -- but i'll find out.
I-i promise.

08:28.275 --> 08:29.508
I'll find out.

08:29.510 --> 08:31.810
You'll find out?
Find out.

08:31.812 --> 08:33.645
[ gasping ]

08:33.647 --> 08:35.547
I'll be back.

08:37.985 --> 08:39.284
[ sobs ]

08:39.286 --> 08:41.119
Elizabeth:
What did you do?

08:41.121 --> 08:42.587
We wanted
a war in west angola.

08:42.589 --> 08:43.822
I'm getting us a war
in west angola.

08:43.824 --> 08:45.056
[ scoffs ]
that's what i did.

08:45.058 --> 08:47.058
By kidnapping
olivia pope?

08:47.060 --> 08:48.760
You need to calm down,
liz.

08:48.762 --> 08:50.061
A man came to my house
last night --

08:50.063 --> 08:52.097
Some henchman
of olivia's.

08:52.099 --> 08:54.966
He threatened me.
He threatened my daughter.

08:54.968 --> 08:57.669
This war was your idea
from day one.

08:57.671 --> 08:59.271
You said it would be good
for the country

08:59.273 --> 09:01.006
And good for the party
and good for<i> us.</i>

09:01.008 --> 09:02.307
[ glass thuds ]

09:02.309 --> 09:03.975
That's what<i> you</i> said,

09:03.977 --> 09:05.977
But now you want to quit the
team in the middle of the game

09:05.979 --> 09:08.680
Because you don't like
the play-calling?

09:08.682 --> 09:10.148
Doesn't work that way.

09:10.150 --> 09:13.985
Winslow is gone, liz.
Kubiak is gone.

09:13.987 --> 09:16.054
It's just you and me.

09:16.055 --> 09:18.122
And i'm gonna be the next
president of the united states.

09:18.125 --> 09:20.825
I don't think
you want to miss that train.

09:20.827 --> 09:23.662
So take a deep breath,
get your head right,

09:23.664 --> 09:25.297
And get the hell
on board.

09:27.801 --> 09:29.968
I'm not recommending
any pardons.

09:29.970 --> 09:31.386
Cyrus:
The man killed jerry grant.

09:31.387 --> 09:32.803
Which is why i'm not
recommending a pardon.

09:32.806 --> 09:33.805
I'm simply...

09:33.807 --> 09:36.575
<i>My name is olivia pope.</i>

09:36.577 --> 09:38.009
<i>I have been taken</i>
<i>against my will.</i>

09:38.011 --> 09:39.344
Abby: [ distant ] why would
the justice department

09:39.346 --> 09:42.097
Even consider a pardon petition
from tom larsen?

09:42.098 --> 09:44.849
[ distant ]
i'm simply bringing the petition
to the president's attention.

09:44.851 --> 09:46.918
[ distant ] well,
now he's aware. Petition denied.

09:46.920 --> 09:49.354
Is that your order,
mr. President?

09:49.356 --> 09:52.724
[<i> voice breaking</i> ]
<i>refuse, and i will be killed.</i>

09:52.726 --> 09:55.026
Abby:
Mr. President?

09:55.028 --> 09:56.227
What?

09:56.229 --> 09:59.064
Just need you to deny
the pardon petition.

09:59.066 --> 10:01.400
Abby:
For tom larsen.

10:01.401 --> 10:03.735
It's ridiculous, absurd,
and offensive, i know,

10:03.737 --> 10:05.537
But the attorney general
seems to think --
oh, again, with the --

10:05.538 --> 10:07.338
I want to see him.
You want to consider
the pardon petition, sir?

10:07.341 --> 10:08.974
For tom larsen?

10:08.976 --> 10:10.559
If the man who killed my son

10:10.560 --> 10:12.143
Is gonna ask me for a pardon,
he can ask me directly.

10:12.145 --> 10:13.878
I want to see him.

10:13.880 --> 10:16.214
Thank you for considering
my petition.

10:16.216 --> 10:18.984
I'm<i> not</i> considering
your petition.

10:18.986 --> 10:20.986
I would<i> never</i> consider pardoning
you for what you did.

10:20.988 --> 10:23.321
I'm sorry about jerry.
I am.

10:23.323 --> 10:24.990
I didn't have anything
against him.

10:24.992 --> 10:26.992
He was a nice boy...

10:26.994 --> 10:29.027
But he was a boy.

10:29.029 --> 10:31.363
And you are a man,

10:31.365 --> 10:33.699
A great man,

10:33.700 --> 10:36.034
And i had to choose between
a nice boy and a great man,

10:36.036 --> 10:39.404
And i chose the great man,
and i am not sorry about that.

10:39.406 --> 10:41.406
I am proud of that.

10:41.408 --> 10:43.041
He was a sacrifice.

10:43.043 --> 10:46.878
<i>I</i> am a sacrifice.

10:46.880 --> 10:50.715
There are sacrifices that need
to be made for greatness,

10:50.717 --> 10:55.086
Brush that needs to be cleared
for the path of history.

11:08.769 --> 11:11.136
I need to know who i can trust
in the white house.

11:13.774 --> 11:16.241
Is that why you're here?
Yes.

11:16.243 --> 11:19.411
In my detail, who can i trust?
Where can i speak privately?

11:19.413 --> 11:21.079
[ chuckles ]

11:21.081 --> 11:24.683
A "face that launched
a thousand ships."

11:24.685 --> 11:27.452
What?
Helen of troy --

11:27.454 --> 11:30.789
Menelaus got her back,
but it took him 10 years of war.

11:30.791 --> 11:34.926
Will you launch a thousand ships
to save miss pope?

11:34.928 --> 11:36.127
You know about this?

11:36.129 --> 11:38.296
Who can you trust
in your detail?

11:38.298 --> 11:40.899
No one.
Where can you speak privately?

11:40.901 --> 11:43.802
The only place you could
ever speak privately.

11:45.439 --> 11:47.706
[ elevator bell dings ]

11:49.976 --> 11:52.177
[ keys jingle ]

11:56.016 --> 11:58.216
I need a minute.

12:09.963 --> 12:11.429
Clever.

12:11.431 --> 12:13.898
It wasn't my idea.
It was agent larsen's.

12:13.900 --> 12:16.134
Tom?

12:16.135 --> 12:18.369
The people who took olivia
are all over me, everywhere.

12:18.371 --> 12:21.106
Except here.
He reminded me of that.

12:21.108 --> 12:23.108
I got it this morning --
proof of life.

12:23.110 --> 12:24.109
How is she?

12:24.111 --> 12:26.978
Alive for
the next two days.

12:26.980 --> 12:29.347
I can't make a move,
or they're gonna kill her.

12:29.349 --> 12:31.015
I'll delay going to war
as long as possible,

12:31.017 --> 12:32.884
But you
need to find her.

12:32.886 --> 12:35.120
Do this within
the next forty...

12:35.122 --> 12:36.821
...Forty-eight hours...

12:36.823 --> 12:39.023
[ voice breaking ]
refuse, and i will be killed.

12:39.025 --> 12:41.760
...Killed.
Declare war...War.

12:41.762 --> 12:44.529
Refuse, and i will be killed.

12:44.531 --> 12:49.200
<i>Do this within</i>
<i>the next 48 hours,</i>

12:49.202 --> 12:51.336
<i>And no harm will come to me.</i>

12:51.338 --> 12:54.139
[<i> voice breaking</i> ]
<i>refuse, and i will be killed.</i>

12:54.141 --> 12:56.040
Is there a coded message?

12:56.042 --> 12:57.942
There's no unusual syntax
or repeated phrases.

12:57.944 --> 12:59.811
I can't find any sign
of a cipher.

12:59.813 --> 13:01.112
What about a location?

13:01.114 --> 13:02.447
The room is windowless,
so no changes in light,

13:02.449 --> 13:04.983
And the microphone never
picks up any ambient sound.

13:04.985 --> 13:06.518
There's no way of telling
where this is filmed.

13:06.520 --> 13:07.986
Play it again.

13:07.988 --> 13:10.188
[ rewinding ]

13:14.928 --> 13:16.528
Did you see that?

13:16.530 --> 13:18.429
No.
What?

13:18.431 --> 13:20.181
That.

13:20.182 --> 13:21.932
She takes a drink of water,
17 seconds,

13:21.935 --> 13:23.468
Then holds the glass up
for four seconds.

13:23.470 --> 13:26.104
So?

13:28.074 --> 13:30.241
Jake: Okay,
what are we looking at?
That.

13:30.243 --> 13:32.377
She's showing us a reflection
in the glass.

13:32.379 --> 13:34.179
That's why she asked
for the water.

13:34.181 --> 13:37.982
[ crying ] i need...
A glass of water, please.

13:40.353 --> 13:43.354
That's our guy.
Can you enhance it?

13:43.356 --> 13:45.356
Uh, there's too much data loss
at this magnification.

13:45.358 --> 13:47.225
I can use the adjoining
frames of video

13:47.226 --> 13:49.093
To create a re-pixelated
composite image.

13:49.095 --> 13:50.428
Might be good enough
to form an i.D.

13:50.430 --> 13:52.463
She's dropping
bread crumbs.

13:59.406 --> 14:01.973
You could wait
outside the door.

14:01.975 --> 14:04.976
And have you find a way to make
a weapon from the toilet seat?

14:04.978 --> 14:07.345
I don't think so.

14:07.347 --> 14:12.884
It's not going to work --
using me as bait.

14:12.886 --> 14:14.018
He won't do it --

14:14.020 --> 14:15.353
Go to war.

14:15.355 --> 14:17.322
The president doesn't
negotiate with terrorists.

14:17.324 --> 14:21.993
Honestly, i don't care.
I get paid either way.

14:21.995 --> 14:23.862
But for argument's sake,
let's wager.

14:23.864 --> 14:28.333
$1 -- i bet you that
he will go to war for you.

14:28.335 --> 14:30.501
$1 says he does it.

14:30.503 --> 14:32.971
Because president or not,
he's just a man --

14:32.973 --> 14:35.139
A sad, terrified man

14:35.141 --> 14:37.976
Who's lost his olivia doll
and wants her back.

14:37.978 --> 14:39.143
Call me a romantic,

14:39.145 --> 14:42.180
But i wager a dollar
that he loves you,

14:42.182 --> 14:44.015
And that's what makes
the world go 'round --

14:44.017 --> 14:49.053
Emotion, sex,
jealousy, insecurities.

14:49.055 --> 14:52.023
Bush invaded iraq
to avenge his daddy.

14:52.025 --> 14:54.559
Clinton bombed serbia
so we'd forget about monica.

14:54.561 --> 14:58.196
Napoleon -- well...
[ laughs ]

14:58.198 --> 15:01.933
Napoleon...
[ laughs ]

15:01.935 --> 15:04.602
[ sighs ]

15:04.604 --> 15:06.204
The president
will go to war, olivia,

15:06.206 --> 15:09.073
And he will
meet our demands.

15:09.075 --> 15:11.042
History says so.
Love says so.

15:11.044 --> 15:13.044
<i>I</i> say so.

15:13.046 --> 15:16.581
I'll wager you that.

15:16.583 --> 15:19.017
Is it a bet?

15:28.094 --> 15:30.094
"their demands."

15:30.096 --> 15:32.230
What?

15:32.231 --> 15:34.365
You said
he'd meet<i> our</i> demands,

15:34.367 --> 15:36.301
Which would be accurate

15:36.302 --> 15:38.236
If you were the one calling
the shots, but you're not.

15:38.238 --> 15:42.941
Out there, someone else
has the power,<i> real</i> power.

15:42.943 --> 15:45.610
They make the demands.
You follow orders.

15:45.612 --> 15:48.346
You're a pawn,
a puppet.

15:48.348 --> 15:50.348
[ chuckles ]

15:50.350 --> 15:53.518
[ inhales sharply ]

15:53.520 --> 16:00.291
You<i> are</i> a pretty thing,
aren't you, huh?

16:00.293 --> 16:03.628
[ breathes deeply ]
it would be such a shame

16:03.630 --> 16:08.633
To return you damaged,
wouldn't it?

16:08.635 --> 16:10.134
Now...

16:10.136 --> 16:13.137
If you're not dressed
and ready to go in 30 seconds,

16:13.139 --> 16:16.107
This is the last bath
you'll get.

16:27.754 --> 16:29.371
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

16:29.372 --> 16:30.989
Qr-10 facial recognition
isn't picking anything up.

16:30.991 --> 16:33.324
He breaks in and scoops up liv
in less than 30 seconds.

16:33.326 --> 16:34.876
The guy's a pro.

16:34.877 --> 16:36.427
He's got to be
on a database somewhere.

16:36.429 --> 16:37.595
Well, i can reach out
to foreign contacts --

16:37.597 --> 16:39.630
Interpol, mossad, mi6.

16:39.632 --> 16:41.332
Excuse me?
Where's the black lady?

16:41.334 --> 16:42.633
Quinn: What?

16:42.635 --> 16:45.036
The black lady,
the one in charge.

16:45.038 --> 16:46.254
Olivia's not here
right now.

16:46.255 --> 16:47.471
Can -- can we help you
with something?

16:47.474 --> 16:48.740
I want to talk
to the black lady.

16:48.742 --> 16:51.009
Olivia may not be back
for a while.

16:51.011 --> 16:52.310
If you give me
your name...

16:52.312 --> 16:54.746
My name is rose,
and how long is "a while"?

16:54.748 --> 16:56.381
Are you sure
i can't help you, rose?

16:56.383 --> 16:59.017
[ sighs ]
are you the black lady?
No.

16:59.019 --> 17:02.153
Then you can't help me,
can you? I'll be back tomorrow.

17:07.761 --> 17:09.327
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

17:09.329 --> 17:10.795
4 of west angola's
10 most populous areas

17:10.797 --> 17:12.163
Are under rebel control.

17:12.165 --> 17:13.798
Air strikes are a nonstarter,

17:13.800 --> 17:17.368
Given the amount of civilian
casualties they'd endure.

17:17.370 --> 17:18.703
Ground troops
give us better odds,

17:18.705 --> 17:21.039
But these two rivers
here and here

17:21.041 --> 17:23.741
Mean we can only approach
from the west and south.

17:23.743 --> 17:26.344
Those rivers are seasonal,
yes?
Correct, mr. President.

17:26.346 --> 17:28.813
So waiting
the four to six weeks

17:28.815 --> 17:31.049
For dry season to begin --
andrew: Four to six weeks?

17:31.051 --> 17:32.183
Excuse me for talking
out of turn,

17:32.185 --> 17:33.818
But that's too long
a wait.

17:33.820 --> 17:37.622
I'm making sure our soldiers
don't walk into an ambush.

17:37.624 --> 17:39.435
And if we wait for the rivers
to run dry,

17:39.436 --> 17:41.247
How do we know the rebels
won't use that time

17:41.248 --> 17:43.059
To plot and execute another
attack on our home soil?

17:43.063 --> 17:45.096
You're talking
about hypothetical risks.

17:45.098 --> 17:46.664
Tell that to the shrapnel
in my ass.

17:46.665 --> 17:48.231
Mr. Vice president,
i think that's --

17:48.234 --> 17:49.767
Your room, your call,
mr. President.

17:49.769 --> 17:54.405
I'd just hate for you to forget
that waiting has consequences.

17:57.177 --> 17:59.844
Cyrus?

17:59.846 --> 18:02.413
Cyrus?

18:02.415 --> 18:05.483
Cyrus.

18:05.485 --> 18:07.785
Flacks at state are asking
who's on the list

18:07.787 --> 18:09.654
For the coalition
for west angola.

18:09.656 --> 18:10.788
What's your point?

18:10.790 --> 18:13.324
My point is, um,
who is on the list

18:13.326 --> 18:14.659
For the coalition
for west angola?

18:14.661 --> 18:16.527
Fitz hates
the vice president.

18:16.529 --> 18:19.764
We<i> all</i> hate
the vice president.

18:19.766 --> 18:22.133
Anyway,
the list for the coalition?

18:22.135 --> 18:23.835
So why is
he listening to him?

18:23.837 --> 18:25.403
Why is the vice president
listening to who?

18:25.405 --> 18:26.737
Why is fitz listening
to the vice president?

18:26.739 --> 18:28.423
Why is the vice president
suddenly in?

18:28.424 --> 18:30.108
The vice president
is<i> not</i> in.

18:30.110 --> 18:32.743
I'm out.
He is not listening to me.

18:32.745 --> 18:34.278
Everything is fine.

18:34.280 --> 18:36.881
For once, everything
around here is fine.

18:36.883 --> 18:38.416
Red...
[ breathes shakily ]

18:38.418 --> 18:40.251
...I don't know
who is on the list

18:40.253 --> 18:41.853
For the coalition
for west angola.

18:41.855 --> 18:44.689
I didn't know there was
a coalition for west angola.

18:47.360 --> 18:48.893
Oh.

18:50.763 --> 18:52.296
[ sighs ]

18:52.298 --> 18:54.799
Get out. Get out!
Now.

18:54.801 --> 18:56.200
[ sighing ]

19:01.608 --> 19:03.207
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

19:10.817 --> 19:12.583
[ computer beeps ]

19:13.853 --> 19:15.386
It failed.

19:15.388 --> 19:16.888
Do it again.

19:16.890 --> 19:18.707
I ran it 22 times.

19:18.708 --> 19:20.525
Qr-10 doesn't recognize
the facial image.

19:20.527 --> 19:22.260
No chatter?
No chatter.

19:22.262 --> 19:23.361
Nothing
from your contacts?

19:23.363 --> 19:24.929
Nothing.

19:27.267 --> 19:28.833
[ sighs ]

19:28.835 --> 19:31.169
Where are you going?

19:31.171 --> 19:33.271
Where are<i> you</i> going?

19:35.675 --> 19:36.908
Huck.

19:40.180 --> 19:41.746
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

19:43.349 --> 19:46.751
[ sighs ]

19:59.599 --> 20:01.265
[ gasps ]

20:01.267 --> 20:02.900
If you scream,
i'll break her neck.

20:02.902 --> 20:04.368
Snap it like a twig.

20:06.673 --> 20:08.806
You didn't do
what you promised, lizzie.

20:08.808 --> 20:11.876
If you hurt my daughter,
olivia pope is dead.

20:11.878 --> 20:13.844
True.

20:13.846 --> 20:17.381
So...

20:17.383 --> 20:18.950
What to do?

20:18.952 --> 20:21.352
What to do?

20:25.458 --> 20:27.892
[ gasps ]

20:27.894 --> 20:29.727
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

20:34.901 --> 20:36.901
[ indistinct conversations ]

20:50.516 --> 20:54.352
Good night, sir.

20:54.354 --> 20:56.721
Good night.

21:00.493 --> 21:04.028
[ sighs ] fitz,
are you coming to bed?

21:05.732 --> 21:07.565
If you think
you have the right

21:07.567 --> 21:11.469
To be mad
about me and andrew...

21:13.973 --> 21:16.507
What is it?
What's going on?

21:16.509 --> 21:20.578
What is going<i> on?</i>

21:27.420 --> 21:29.654
[ sighs ]

21:44.370 --> 21:46.604
Fitz, what are you --

21:48.841 --> 21:50.841
Fitz.

21:50.843 --> 21:52.009
In 24 hours,

21:52.011 --> 21:54.679
I'm gonna
kill olivia pope.

21:54.681 --> 21:57.682
What?

21:57.684 --> 22:00.584
Andrew has her --
somewhere.

22:00.586 --> 22:01.819
I don't know where.

22:01.821 --> 22:04.989
But if i don't send troops
to west angola,

22:04.991 --> 22:06.891
She will be killed.

22:06.893 --> 22:08.426
[ inhales sharply ]

22:08.428 --> 22:10.428
It's a coup.

22:10.430 --> 22:11.829
Your boyfriend

22:11.831 --> 22:15.599
Has orchestrated
a bona-fide american coup.

22:17.904 --> 22:20.905
And what kind of president
would i be?

22:20.907 --> 22:22.606
[ sighs ]

22:22.608 --> 22:27.611
What kind of monument --
if i indulged in this war?

22:27.613 --> 22:29.947
If i sent thousands of people
to their deaths

22:29.949 --> 22:31.649
To save the life
of one person

22:31.651 --> 22:33.551
No matter who that person
is to me.

22:33.553 --> 22:36.354
I can't do that.

22:36.356 --> 22:38.723
[ sighs ]
right?

22:38.725 --> 22:43.561
Our son died
so i could stay in office,

22:43.563 --> 22:45.029
So how can i
dishonor him now

22:45.031 --> 22:47.631
By giving in and negotiating
with terrorists,

22:47.633 --> 22:49.633
Even if it means liv dies?

22:49.635 --> 22:51.469
I can't do it.

22:51.471 --> 22:53.471
[ sighs ]

22:53.473 --> 22:54.872
Right?

23:00.113 --> 23:02.880
I thought you loved her.

23:04.951 --> 23:06.951
Don't tell me we've been through
all of this

23:06.953 --> 23:08.953
For a cheap screw.

23:08.955 --> 23:12.590
I love her.

23:18.998 --> 23:21.766
Then you know
what you have to do.

23:39.419 --> 23:41.752
Fitz:
My fellow americans,

23:41.754 --> 23:45.656
Moments ago, under my orders...

23:45.658 --> 23:48.859
<i>American forces began</i>
<i>their first stages</i>

23:48.861 --> 23:52.129
<i>Of military operations in the</i>
<i>effort to free west angola...</i>

23:52.131 --> 23:53.998
Don't do it. Don't.

23:54.000 --> 23:56.467
<i>...From those who would replace</i>
<i>its freedoms and democracy</i>

23:56.469 --> 23:58.102
With tyranny...
[ camera shutters clicking ]

23:58.104 --> 24:00.771
...From those responsible
for attacking

24:00.773 --> 24:03.941
Our vice president
on our own soil.

24:03.943 --> 24:06.444
These attacks
are the opening stages

24:06.445 --> 24:08.946
Of what will be a broad
and concerted campaign

24:08.948 --> 24:11.916
Against the rebel forces
in west angola.

24:11.918 --> 24:13.918
To protect our nation...

24:13.920 --> 24:15.786
Is this
really happening?

24:15.788 --> 24:18.088
It's really happening.

24:18.090 --> 24:20.991
...And the very idea
of our existence.

24:20.993 --> 24:25.162
<i>We face an enemy with no regard</i>
<i>for the conventions of war,</i>

24:25.164 --> 24:26.864
<i>An enemy that will not hesitate</i>

24:26.866 --> 24:29.500
<i>To use innocent civilians</i>
<i>as shields.</i>

24:29.502 --> 24:32.837
We cannot allow them
to have the last word.

24:32.839 --> 24:36.507
And i promise you, they won't.

24:36.509 --> 24:38.843
May god bless and protect

24:38.845 --> 24:40.878
The men and women
of our armed forces.

24:40.880 --> 24:42.847
<i>And may god</i>
<i>continue to bless...</i>
And may god continue to bless...

24:42.848 --> 24:44.815
The united states of america.
<i>...The united states</i>
<i>of america.</i>

24:44.817 --> 24:47.485
[<i> reporters shouting</i> ]

24:47.487 --> 24:49.687
Who's the puppet now?

25:03.870 --> 25:05.703
That was
very nicely done.

25:08.574 --> 25:10.908
Where is she?

25:10.910 --> 25:12.576
I know it was difficult
for you.

25:12.578 --> 25:15.746
You got your war.
Now let her go.

25:15.748 --> 25:18.549
Fitz, come on.

25:18.551 --> 25:20.885
We both know a round
of drone strikes

25:20.887 --> 25:22.953
Does not
constitute a war.

25:22.955 --> 25:25.256
And if olivia pope
were back here right now,

25:25.258 --> 25:26.790
She'd have you
out of west angola

25:26.792 --> 25:27.858
By the end of the day.

25:27.860 --> 25:31.695
Wars take time.
[ liquid pouring ]

25:31.697 --> 25:33.163
And we need that time
if we're gonna get

25:33.165 --> 25:36.534
Your second term
back on track.

25:36.536 --> 25:38.836
We've got a lot
of work to do.

25:38.838 --> 25:41.005
But there's no limit
to what we can accomplish

25:41.007 --> 25:44.775
If we do it together.

25:46.546 --> 25:48.546
[ sighs ]

25:48.548 --> 25:50.881
We'll have to regain
the party's trust, of course,

25:50.883 --> 25:52.182
Which will mean
rolling back gun control

25:52.184 --> 25:53.751
And equal pay,
education.

25:53.753 --> 25:56.053
And then there's
defense spending.

25:56.055 --> 25:58.756
You're never gonna let her go,
are you?

25:58.758 --> 25:59.957
Honestly?

25:59.959 --> 26:03.861
That depends entirely...

26:03.863 --> 26:05.062
[ glass thuds ]
...On you.

26:07.166 --> 26:08.799
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

26:08.801 --> 26:11.101
The black lady --
she's still not here?

26:11.103 --> 26:13.070
Look,
i'm sorry, ma'am,

26:13.072 --> 26:15.172
If you could just tell me
what the problem is --

26:15.174 --> 26:17.007
I gave my friend lois
a medical-alert bracelet

26:17.009 --> 26:19.944
A couple of years ago
right after john passed.

26:19.946 --> 26:22.279
But do you think she'd ever
bother to wear it?

26:22.281 --> 26:25.115
No.
Said it made her feel old.

26:25.117 --> 26:26.650
Well, we<i> are</i> old.

26:26.652 --> 26:28.652
And now she's missing,

26:28.654 --> 26:30.821
And i have no way
to try to find her.

26:30.823 --> 26:34.024
That's why i need to talk
to the black lady.

26:34.026 --> 26:36.694
She's the one who knows lois.
Wait. Who's lois?

26:36.696 --> 26:38.162
Lois is my friend.

26:38.164 --> 26:41.699
She won't answer her door,
her phone.

26:41.701 --> 26:43.033
Her car is still
in her garage.

26:43.035 --> 26:45.369
She gave the black lady
her spare key.

26:45.371 --> 26:48.105
Lois always said
she was nice, trustworthy,

26:48.107 --> 26:49.807
And helped people
for a living.

26:49.809 --> 26:52.076
Hold on.

26:52.077 --> 26:54.344
Why does the black --
olivia have lois' key?

26:54.347 --> 26:56.246
She lives right across
the hall from her,

26:56.248 --> 26:59.783
But i've knocked on that door
a hundred times.

26:59.785 --> 27:01.986
[ sighs ] and i guess
she's missing, too.

27:14.634 --> 27:17.034
Nothing in the kitchen.

27:19.271 --> 27:21.271
Maybe she wasn't here.
She was here.

27:22.008 --> 27:23.407
[ ring clatters ]

27:24.043 --> 27:26.243
Are you sure
that it's liv's?

27:26.245 --> 27:28.879
Oh, she wears it for him.
She never takes it off.

27:28.881 --> 27:31.715
So she was here.
She left it for us to find.

27:31.717 --> 27:33.951
Breadcrumbs.

27:33.953 --> 27:35.352
They were watching
liv's apartment from here.

27:35.354 --> 27:36.787
You'd need monitors,
sound.

27:36.788 --> 27:38.221
You could do a whole setup
with a hand truck.

27:38.224 --> 27:41.258
Easy in, easy out.
Maybe use a cell signal?

27:41.260 --> 27:42.793
No, this building is old.
The walls are thick.

27:42.795 --> 27:44.428
The plumbing is copper.

27:44.429 --> 27:46.062
You couldn't rely on a cell
signal for precision work.

27:46.065 --> 27:48.932
So you'd need
an internet connection.

27:48.934 --> 27:50.868
Like that.

27:52.972 --> 27:55.406
You think
you can figure out

27:55.408 --> 27:57.441
Who was the last person
to log into this network?

27:59.712 --> 28:01.078
[ keyboard clacking ]

28:01.080 --> 28:02.713
Got something!

28:04.083 --> 28:07.084
An unauthorized intrusion
into the neighbor's wi-fi.

28:07.086 --> 28:09.019
The i.P.'s registered
to this guy.

28:09.021 --> 28:11.138
That's not the guy
from the water glass.

28:11.139 --> 28:13.256
Check for known associates.
[ keyboard clacking ]

28:13.259 --> 28:16.093
There.
That's the guy in the glass.

28:16.095 --> 28:17.728
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

28:17.729 --> 28:19.362
Huck: Got him -- ian woods,
a.K.A. Claude jolie,

28:19.365 --> 28:20.964
A.K.A. Martin st. John.

28:20.966 --> 28:22.399
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

28:26.839 --> 28:31.141
I want you to take a look at
this n.S.C. Report on the war.

28:31.143 --> 28:32.710
See if it does
a good enough job outlining

28:32.711 --> 28:34.278
Our long-term strategy before
it's released to the media.

28:34.280 --> 28:35.946
I don't need to read
that report.

28:35.948 --> 28:38.982
I want to hear
your thoughts.

28:41.320 --> 28:44.855
Take the report,
cyrus.

28:44.857 --> 28:46.490
You want to hear
my thoughts?

28:46.492 --> 28:48.025
Really? Now?

28:48.027 --> 28:50.327
After you sent 15,000 troops
into west angola,

28:50.329 --> 28:53.464
After you went on tv and told
this nation we were at war,

28:53.466 --> 28:57.134
After all that,
you want to hear my...

28:57.136 --> 28:58.769
Thoughts?

28:58.771 --> 29:01.004
Thank you for asking, sir.
28 men and 3 women.

29:01.006 --> 29:05.008
That's how many casualties
this war has cost us already.

29:05.010 --> 29:06.593
My thoughts
are with them --

29:06.594 --> 29:08.177
The 31 service members
who have lost their lives

29:08.180 --> 29:10.013
In an unnecessary war.

29:10.015 --> 29:12.182
Does your report
even mention their names?

29:12.184 --> 29:13.517
Does it reveal
the reason why

29:13.519 --> 29:16.487
They were sent into battle
in the first place?

29:16.489 --> 29:20.858
'cause i sure as hell
don't know it.

29:20.860 --> 29:23.494
There you have it, sir --
my thoughts.

29:23.496 --> 29:27.931
Some meaningless p.R. Document
isn't going to change them.

29:32.071 --> 29:34.972
[ papers thud ]

29:36.876 --> 29:40.844
Take this report back
to your office...

29:40.846 --> 29:43.380
And<i> read</i> it.

29:54.059 --> 29:57.060
[ door creaks ]

29:57.062 --> 29:58.128
[ sighs ]

30:01.867 --> 30:03.967
I want beef stew.

30:03.969 --> 30:05.903
Well, that wasn't one
of today's specials.

30:05.905 --> 30:09.273
Beef stew.

30:09.275 --> 30:13.043
And then i would like an orange
creamsicle for dessert.

30:13.045 --> 30:14.478
Orange --
that's important.

30:14.480 --> 30:17.147
I know they have the others --
blue-raspberry, lime --

30:17.149 --> 30:19.983
But i grew up
on the orange ones.

30:19.985 --> 30:21.151
This is the meal
i would like,

30:21.153 --> 30:23.420
Then i would like to be shot
in the head!

30:23.422 --> 30:24.972
You want to be shot
in the head?

30:24.973 --> 30:26.523
Yes.
Why would you
be shot in the head?

30:26.525 --> 30:30.060
Because i'm going to die,
and i want to decide how!

30:30.062 --> 30:31.528
They've got their war.

30:31.530 --> 30:34.364
I've seen your face.
You<i> have</i> to kill me.

30:34.366 --> 30:35.532
I know how this works.

30:35.534 --> 30:37.367
Oh, olivia.

30:37.369 --> 30:40.437
I'm so sorry.
You've got this all wrong.

30:40.439 --> 30:45.209
I'm not gonna kill you,
not anytime soon.

30:45.211 --> 30:48.212
This is a long-term gig

30:48.214 --> 30:51.081
For at least
the next three years or so,

30:51.083 --> 30:53.050
Until the end
of the president's term.

30:53.052 --> 30:55.385
But after that, sure, yeah,
i'll have to kill you,

30:55.387 --> 30:57.020
But that's so far
down the road

30:57.022 --> 31:00.858
There's no point in really
even talking about it now.

31:00.860 --> 31:02.993
You shouldn't have
killed otto.

31:02.995 --> 31:05.162
He was the chef,

31:05.164 --> 31:09.366
But i will see what i can do
about that creamsicle.

31:15.941 --> 31:19.009
Huck: We gave ian woods'
sat phone a ping.

31:19.011 --> 31:20.461
It'll respond by connecting
to the nearest satellite.

31:20.462 --> 31:21.912
So...
Satellites
are geo-synchronous.

31:21.914 --> 31:23.347
They always fly over
the same place.

31:23.349 --> 31:24.882
So we find the satellite,
we find liv.

31:24.884 --> 31:25.883
Morocco.

31:25.885 --> 31:27.885
Got her!

31:27.887 --> 31:28.986
No, wait.
She's in cambodia.

31:28.988 --> 31:31.889
Havana?
What's going on?

31:31.891 --> 31:34.091
He's bouncing
his cellphone's signal

31:34.093 --> 31:36.260
Across the entire
satellite network.

31:36.262 --> 31:37.928
She could be
in any of these locations.

31:37.930 --> 31:40.264
There's no way to find her.

31:42.268 --> 31:45.569
[ knock on door ]

31:45.571 --> 31:48.238
Yeah?

31:48.240 --> 31:50.941
Elizabeth.
[ laughs ]

31:50.943 --> 31:52.376
I thought you
and the vice president

31:52.378 --> 31:55.078
Would be off rutting somewhere,
celebrating your victory.

31:55.080 --> 31:58.415
That's why i'm here.

31:58.417 --> 32:02.319
I have<i> nothing</i> to do
with this.

32:02.321 --> 32:03.687
You have to
believe me.

32:03.689 --> 32:05.923
Oh, feeling squeamish?
I don't blame you.

32:05.925 --> 32:08.025
Kidnapping's a felony,
after all.

32:08.027 --> 32:10.928
A man broke into my house
last night --

32:10.930 --> 32:14.331
One of olivia's people.
What did you expect?

32:14.333 --> 32:16.333
You didn't think they'd do
everything in their power

32:16.335 --> 32:17.935
To get their precious
olivia back?

32:17.937 --> 32:21.038
Everything in their power?
Huh?

32:21.040 --> 32:24.708
You mean like this?

32:24.710 --> 32:25.709
[ gasps ]

32:25.711 --> 32:29.212
Oh. Ohh.

32:37.990 --> 32:42.492
He'll kill me
if she doesn't come back.

32:42.494 --> 32:46.997
He'll find me,
and he'll kill me.

32:46.999 --> 32:51.001
Well,
olivia will come back.

32:51.003 --> 32:53.503
Andrew's getting his war.
They'll have to release her.

32:53.505 --> 32:55.038
She'll be back.

32:55.040 --> 32:57.374
You're smart, mellie,
and you know andrew.

32:57.376 --> 32:59.443
Do you really think
he's gonna stop at the war,

32:59.445 --> 33:01.478
Or do you think that
now that he has olivia pope --

33:01.480 --> 33:04.147
Now that he realizes
how much she's worth --

33:04.149 --> 33:06.149
He's just gonna keep demanding
and demanding

33:06.151 --> 33:08.051
Until none of us
have anything left to give?

33:08.053 --> 33:10.454
[ sighs ]

33:10.456 --> 33:13.457
I'm sure we'll keep that in mind
when we're awarding contracts.

33:13.459 --> 33:17.160
But for now, senator,

33:17.162 --> 33:19.329
Our focus is the people
of west angola.

33:19.331 --> 33:21.665
Right.

33:21.667 --> 33:24.167
Thank you.
Good night, senator.

33:24.169 --> 33:25.335
[ receiver clicks ]

33:25.337 --> 33:27.004
You're working
late tonight.

33:27.006 --> 33:28.005
[ sighs ]

33:28.007 --> 33:30.040
The, uh,
president asked me to --

33:30.042 --> 33:33.276
Give him back
olivia pope.

33:33.278 --> 33:35.278
He told you that?

33:35.280 --> 33:37.080
What are your intentions,
andrew?

33:37.082 --> 33:38.248
Whose side are you on?

33:38.250 --> 33:41.018
Whose side?
Is it gonna be you and me,

33:41.020 --> 33:42.285
Or are you
and elizabeth north

33:42.287 --> 33:44.221
Planning to ride off
into the oval together?

33:44.223 --> 33:45.389
Because if that's the case --
listen to me.

33:45.391 --> 33:47.391
Listen to me.
[ sighs ]

33:47.393 --> 33:49.126
Elizabeth was a mistake.
Hmm.

33:49.128 --> 33:51.595
Fitz forced us
to stop seeing each other.
No.

33:51.597 --> 33:53.430
Fitz forced you
to make a choice,

33:53.432 --> 33:54.731
And you made
your choice.

33:54.733 --> 33:56.800
And it was
the wrong one.

33:56.802 --> 33:58.802
Believe me.

33:58.804 --> 34:03.073
None of this means anything
to me, mel, without you.

34:03.075 --> 34:07.477
It's gonna be you and me
in the oval.

34:07.479 --> 34:12.382
From now on,
it's you and me.

34:23.595 --> 34:27.330
We have to rethink our media
strategy for this war, cyrus.

34:27.332 --> 34:28.832
This is shark week,
and i'm the chum.

34:28.834 --> 34:30.834
Ron ziegler.

34:30.836 --> 34:32.569
From the nixon
administration?

34:32.570 --> 34:34.303
He had to explain vietnam
every night for years --

34:34.306 --> 34:36.006
A master at his craft.

34:36.007 --> 34:37.707
Don't you want to be a master
at your craft, red?

34:37.709 --> 34:40.343
Depends -- do i get to go
back in time to a world
before the internet

34:40.345 --> 34:42.079
And twitter and everything else
that makes my job

34:42.081 --> 34:44.081
About a thousand times harder
than ron ziegler's.

34:44.083 --> 34:45.482
[ distant ] cyrus?

34:46.685 --> 34:49.086
Take the report, cyrus.

34:49.087 --> 34:51.488
Moments ago, american forces
began their first stages...
Is this really happening?

34:51.490 --> 34:53.490
It's really happening.

34:53.492 --> 34:55.158
...In the effort
to free west angola.

34:55.160 --> 34:56.793
I need you to gather
the joint chiefs

34:56.795 --> 34:58.095
First thing
in the morning.

34:58.097 --> 34:59.729
Are we talking
about west angola?

35:08.707 --> 35:11.108
Thought you should see
the damage you've wrought.

35:11.110 --> 35:13.543
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

35:13.545 --> 35:15.312
Thank god
for those policies, eh?

35:15.314 --> 35:17.747
Really keeping us honest.

35:20.652 --> 35:23.153
What do you want?

35:23.155 --> 35:26.223
What do i want?
[ chuckles ]

35:28.660 --> 35:30.827
It's the first question
i ask my clients.

35:30.829 --> 35:32.829
Typically, i know what
the answer's going to be,

35:32.831 --> 35:34.798
But i just need them to arrive
at it themselves.

35:34.800 --> 35:36.600
And if i were
one of your clients,

35:36.602 --> 35:38.335
What do you think
i'd say?

35:38.337 --> 35:42.506
You'd say you want power,
but i think that's a lie.

35:42.508 --> 35:45.842
Oh?
And why would that be?

35:45.844 --> 35:47.811
Because you're sitting on one of
the most valuable assets

35:47.813 --> 35:51.548
In the world
and not using it.

35:53.285 --> 35:56.820
Imagine the price i'd fetch
on the open market.

35:56.822 --> 36:01.558
"own olivia pope,
you own the president."

36:01.560 --> 36:02.759
Make that known,

36:02.761 --> 36:05.695
You're the most powerful man
in the world.

36:05.697 --> 36:08.498
Nations, dictators,
drug cartels --

36:08.500 --> 36:10.367
They'd all come running.

36:10.369 --> 36:12.269
You'd be rich
beyond your wildest dreams,

36:12.271 --> 36:14.204
But, no, you'd rather
honor your contract,

36:14.206 --> 36:16.573
Spend the next three years
bringing me food and water.

36:16.575 --> 36:18.492
Yes, you'd be
the highest-paid babysitter

36:18.493 --> 36:20.410
On the planet, but that's all
you'd be -- a babysitter.

36:20.412 --> 36:22.412
You're saying
i should sell you.

36:22.414 --> 36:24.347
I'm saying
<i>we</i> should sell me.

36:24.349 --> 36:27.384
I know the market,
how it operates,

36:27.386 --> 36:29.419
Who the players are,
how to pull their strings.

36:29.421 --> 36:30.937
This is my wheelhouse.

36:30.938 --> 36:32.454
If anyone can make this work
for you, it's me.

36:32.457 --> 36:34.391
So i get rich,
and you get what?

36:34.393 --> 36:35.892
I get to not spend
the next three years

36:35.894 --> 36:38.395
Counting down the days till
the president leaves office

36:38.397 --> 36:39.863
And you put a bullet
in my head.

36:39.865 --> 36:42.299
We both know i'm resourceful.
You get rich.

36:42.301 --> 36:44.301
I get to take my chances
on the open market.

36:44.303 --> 36:46.836
Plus, you'd have to make me look
presentable to get top dollar.

36:46.838 --> 36:48.772
And right now,
i could really use a shower

36:48.774 --> 36:50.674
And a change of clothes.
Think about it, ian.

36:50.676 --> 36:52.342
It's win-win.

36:52.344 --> 36:55.812
But again, the question
isn't what i want.

36:55.814 --> 36:58.048
It's what<i> you</i> want.

36:58.049 --> 37:00.283
Do you want to be a babysitter,
or do you want to be a boss?

37:03.255 --> 37:05.288
It's up to you.

37:10.829 --> 37:13.496
[ sighs ]

37:13.498 --> 37:14.798
Mr. President.

37:14.800 --> 37:17.968
Cyrus.
You read the report?

37:17.970 --> 37:19.970
I read the report.

37:19.972 --> 37:23.340
Well [sighs]
do you have any thoughts?

37:23.342 --> 37:24.774
Was the message clear?

37:24.776 --> 37:26.776
Exceedingly clear,
sir.

37:26.778 --> 37:28.912
I appreciate you sharing it
with me.

37:28.914 --> 37:30.247
[ footsteps approach ]

37:30.249 --> 37:31.248
Gentlemen.

37:31.250 --> 37:32.783
Evening, mellie.

37:32.784 --> 37:34.317
It's cold out here tonight. You
want me to get you your sweater?

37:34.319 --> 37:37.487
I'm fine.

37:37.489 --> 37:39.623
I took care
of everything.

37:46.465 --> 37:47.897
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

37:52.804 --> 37:56.906
I have something
you want --

37:56.908 --> 37:58.875
The vice president's
cellphones.

37:58.877 --> 38:00.543
I've given you everything
i have.

38:00.545 --> 38:02.445
I've -- i've told you
everything i know.

38:04.816 --> 38:08.785
I never wanted this to happen.
I'm sorry.

38:08.787 --> 38:10.954
Now, please,
leave my family alone.

38:15.560 --> 38:16.726
[ sighs ]

38:16.728 --> 38:17.961
Official white house phone --
nothing here.

38:17.963 --> 38:20.463
This is it.
Repeated calls to ian's number.

38:20.465 --> 38:21.631
Those are the only calls
on the phone.

38:21.633 --> 38:23.300
Got a 717 area code.
Pennsylvania?

38:23.302 --> 38:24.634
The vice president
didn't go buy

38:24.636 --> 38:25.835
A burner phone
in pennsylvania.

38:25.837 --> 38:27.737
Which means
ian got it for him.

38:27.739 --> 38:29.572
Which means he's probably
been working from there.

38:29.574 --> 38:31.408
Pennsylvania? We've been
sitting here hacking
low-orbit satellites,

38:31.410 --> 38:33.743
And she's been a couple hours
up the i-83?

38:33.745 --> 38:34.878
It's smart --
reliable infrastructure,

38:34.880 --> 38:36.613
No customs,
no checkpoints.

38:36.615 --> 38:37.947
There -- one of the satellites
ian's signal bounced off of

38:37.949 --> 38:39.349
Is over harrisburg.

38:39.351 --> 38:40.850
I can use it to zero in
on a location.

38:40.852 --> 38:42.085
Okay,
we're looking for warehouses

38:42.087 --> 38:43.853
Or factories
near major highways,

38:43.855 --> 38:45.722
Isolated but with clear
escape routes.

38:45.724 --> 38:47.957
Oh, what about that?
Looks like
an abandoned airport hangar.

38:47.959 --> 38:49.392
That would work.

38:49.393 --> 38:50.826
Hey, so why aren't
you calling the white house?

38:50.829 --> 38:52.362
If i call the white house,
they'll kill olivia.

38:52.364 --> 38:54.364
They can't go get her.
Then it's the three of us?

38:54.366 --> 38:55.699
Bust in there
and take on

38:55.701 --> 38:58.001
God knows how many armed
mercenaries ourselves?

38:58.003 --> 38:59.035
All right. I'm down.

38:59.037 --> 39:01.938
I have a better idea.

39:01.940 --> 39:05.909
I'm saving olivia pope.
I want you to acknowledge that.
Yes.

39:05.911 --> 39:07.911
I just did.
Do you see this hat?

39:07.913 --> 39:09.779
I don't see a hat.

39:09.781 --> 39:10.814
Use your imagination.

39:10.816 --> 39:12.949
I'm wearing a 10-gallon
white hat.

39:12.951 --> 39:14.417
Just for the record.

39:14.419 --> 39:16.419
Are you done?
I'm done.

39:19.091 --> 39:21.458
David rosen.
We have a drug raid.

39:21.460 --> 39:22.926
Harrisburg,
pennsylvania.

39:22.928 --> 39:25.962
Correct. Warrant is on the way.
Be ready.

39:25.964 --> 39:28.765
D.E.A. Is on board.
You're all set.

39:28.767 --> 39:31.368
I'm saving olivia pope.

40:20.419 --> 40:22.585
Man: Clear!

40:22.587 --> 40:24.821
[ indistinct shouting ]

40:27.759 --> 40:30.794
<i>She's not here.</i>
<i>There's nothing here.</i>

40:31.930 --> 40:33.563
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

40:33.565 --> 40:35.732
Do you think
she's alive?

40:35.734 --> 40:38.568
She's alive.

40:38.570 --> 40:40.637
How do you know?

40:48.013 --> 40:49.145
Woman: Mr. President,
you're looking at footage

40:49.147 --> 40:51.815
Taken by paramedic
helmet cams

40:51.816 --> 40:54.484
Just after first-wave attacks
on the rebels in west angola.
[<i> gunfire</i> ]

40:54.486 --> 40:58.488
33 total americans dead,
11 wounded, 2 missing.

40:58.490 --> 40:59.823
Those are our best numbers

40:59.825 --> 41:02.025
As of 18:00 hours
eastern standard time.

41:02.027 --> 41:04.027
Mr. President?
I have olivia pope for you.

41:07.799 --> 41:08.932
Hi.

41:08.934 --> 41:10.533
Hi.

41:11.837 --> 41:13.703
Hi.

41:13.705 --> 41:15.171
Who's this?

41:15.173 --> 41:17.006
I have what you want.

41:17.008 --> 41:18.975
Put her back on the phone.
Let me talk to her.

41:18.977 --> 41:20.610
Oh, in due time.

41:20.611 --> 41:22.244
I gave you your war.
Let me talk to her.

41:22.247 --> 41:24.814
War?
I don't care about the war.

41:24.816 --> 41:25.849
I'm a businessman,
mr. President.

41:25.851 --> 41:27.451
So let's talk business.

41:27.452 --> 41:29.052
I'm selling ms. Pope
to the highest bidder.

41:29.054 --> 41:30.854
You're welcome to join.

41:30.855 --> 41:32.655
But if i had to guess,
it's gonna cost you.

41:32.657 --> 41:33.857
The woman who controls

41:33.859 --> 41:36.125
The president
of the united states?

41:36.127 --> 41:38.561
She's gonna be worth
quite a bit

41:38.562 --> 41:40.996
To your enemies, your allies --
well, everyone really.

41:40.999 --> 41:43.266
I'll be in touch
once it all starts.

41:43.268 --> 41:45.168
Good luck.

41:48.640 --> 41:49.639
[ computer beeps ]

41:49.641 --> 41:50.874
Quinn!

41:50.876 --> 41:52.208
What?
Chatter.

41:52.210 --> 41:53.543
What?

41:53.545 --> 41:54.544
Chatter!

41:54.546 --> 41:55.879
Where?
Everywhere.

41:55.881 --> 41:56.913
Oh, my god.

41:56.915 --> 41:57.914
This is good.

41:57.916 --> 41:59.566
Good?
How is this good?

41:59.567 --> 42:01.217
Because she's alive,
because we can track her.

42:01.219 --> 42:04.187
She did this.
She's dropping us breadcrumbs.

42:04.189 --> 42:08.057
We just have to
follow them.

42:21.773 --> 42:23.306
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]
